1- Install kitty
sudo apt install kitty

2- Install ZSH
sudo apt install zsh

3- Make zsh as the default shell in the terminal
sudo gedit .bashrc
Add to the end of the file a new line with the following:
exec zsh
write and save changes.

4- Edit the .zshrc with the proper config in the repo.

5- Install the syntax highlighting and the autosuggestions
sudo apt install zsh-syntax-highlighting
sudo apt install zsh-autosuggestions

6- Install the sudo plugin
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/plugins/sudo/sudo.plugin.zsh
Clone this in /usr/share/zsh-sudo

7- Install snap for later packages

sudo apt install snapd

8- Install lsd and bat
 
 sudo snap install lsd
 sudo apt install bat
 
 9- Make some changes to the kitty.conf with the template from https://github.com/rxyhn/dotfiles
 Place the config commands in the kitty.conf file in .config/kitty/kitty.conf
 
 10- Installing fonts
 HackNerdFonts - Install FiraCode
 Add "FiraCode NerdFont" to the font family section
 
 
